    "offer_browser_tts": "false",
    "panels": [
      {
        "text": "### Music Lab\n\nMusic Lab has 2 key areas for making songs:\n- **Toolbox:** these are the blocks you can use to complete a level\n- **Workspace:** This is where the code for your song goes!\n\nYou create music by dragging blocks from the toolbox into the workspace!\n",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/7650cc7d736cb6c7605a8018fe28f980-overview-1c.png",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-practice-play-sequential-panel-77c61549-a2c5-4165-a211-283d47d9b82a",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Selecting Sounds\n\nThe `play` block lets you choose sounds to use in your song:\n\n<span style=\"padding: 2px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-drum\" style=\"color: #E565F5; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Beat </span> - the pulse of the music that makes you want to tap your foot or nod your head.\n\n<span style=\"padding: 2px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-boombox\" style=\"color: #58BEF9; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Bass </span> - the low, deep sounds in a song that makes the music feel full and powerful.\n\n<span style=\"padding: 2px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-guitars\" style=\"color: #64D25A; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Lead </span> - the main tune of the song that you'd most likely hum along to, often played by guitars or synths.\n\n<span style=\"padding: 2px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-waveform\" style=\"color: #F3DF55; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Effect </span> - a special sound for extra flavor, excitement, or to create a specific mood.\n\n<span style=\"padding: 2px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone-stand\" style=\"color: #F99258; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Vocal </span> - the part of the song that is sung by a person.\n\n",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/d89f0682b08cbb4541a2dee5ea5fb9f6-overview-2c.png",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-practice-play-sequential-panel-44ddc497-1a7a-4252-a306-a19ab550d8cf",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Tracks\n\nAfter you pick a sound, it will appear in the timeline as its own **track**. The color of the sounds match the colors of your tracks.\n\n---\n\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i> A **track** is a single layer of sound in a song. When you add a play block to your code, a new track is created for the sound.",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/a644f740017c0412f1f4e52b41bb00eb-overview-4d.png",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-explore-play-sequential-overviewpanel_v2-7a8a8c6f-7428-456d-b4a8-1463a42d1f1a",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Timing\n\nYou can also see how many **measures** the sound is. This helps you plan how sounds will fit together in the **timeline** on the bottom of the screen\n\n---\n\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i> A **measure** is a small segment of music that contains a specific number of beats, usually 4 in pop music.",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/0464105b260714c73073d22ade8823c2-overview-4e.png",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-practice-play-sequential-panel-08943d00-a581-4880-acd6-de0970d8529d",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Adjust The Workspace\n\nYou can use the Zoom In / Zoom Out features of your browser to adjust how Music Lab fits on your screen. This can make it easier to see your code or read the instructions. \n",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/a08216a92e0f72af87fd1b669c9ef855-zoom.gif",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-practice-play-sequential-panel-bf0bbc9c-45a8-4461-b394-d279f7547c56",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true,
        "layout": "text-bottom-right"
      },
      {
        "text": "Key Takeaway: Use play blocks to build your song with different sounds. Each sound has a different length, which determines how long the track appears on the timeline.",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/04a5b1fa7c381840319958686116fb20-overview-6.png",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-practice-play-sequential-panel-c846fce5-8889-4bff-8a48-f717d5302c15",
        "typing": true,
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      }
    ],
    "bubble_choice_description": "Review how to use Play Sequential when creating songs",
